<TITLE> Artist Maqbool Fida 'India's Picasso' no longer Indian </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 08 (bdnews24.com)  Renowned artist Maqbool Fida Husain, once dubbed 'India's Picasso', surrendered his Indian passport on Sunday, media reports said. The 95-year-old Husain, who was recently granted Qatari citizenship, surrendered his Indian passport to the country's mission in Doha, according to the Gulf Times. Husain, who left his homeland for self-imposed exile nearly four years ago following a number of cases in India over his controversial paintings of Hindu goddesses, had accepted Qatar's offer of citizenship, his son Owais Husain recently told the Press Trust of India. India does not recognise dual citizenship. "In such a situation, surrender of passport by the person concerned is mandatory and Husain has done just that," an Indian Embassy official was quoted as saying by P
